# 15. Completion Criteria

Phase 0.6 is considered complete when:

1. This document exists at `docs/Phase-0.6-API-Specification-and-Backend-Contracts.md` and is committed with a `docs:` commit, per the Git Standards in Phase 0.3.
2. Every module listed in Section 7 has a fully written Purpose, Responsibilities, Operations Supported, Expected Behaviour, Ownership, and Dependencies description in Section 8.
3. The standard request rules, response format, and error handling (Sections 4–6) are specific enough that any future endpoint's shape can be inferred directly from this document without inventing new conventions.
4. Authentication and authorization rules (Section 3) leave no endpoint's access level ambiguous.
5. The document contains no backend code, controller signatures, DTOs, or implementation of any kind.
6. The document has been reviewed and explicitly approved by the project owner as the permanent API contract for all subsequent backend and frontend phases.

Once these conditions are met, Phase 0.6 is closed. Actual endpoint implementation begins only in its designated future phase, and must faithfully translate this document into NestJS controllers, services, and DTOs using the technology and data model locked in Phases 0.3 and 0.5.

